findGCSName

public abstract String findGCSName(GeographicCoordinateSystem gcs)
Retrieves the GCS from the database if one exists. This uses the datum name within the specified GCS along with the inherent PrimeMeridian to search by PE Datum Names. This is used in conjunction with PE CoordSys strings.

Parameters:
gcs -
Returns:
null if none exists otherwise returns the GCS name within the database
